# Testing

High quality is a hard requirement, so **test where it adds value**. Favour a small number of
fast, meaningful tests over chasing a coverage number. See `docs/testing.md` for the full
rationale.

## Stack

- **Vitest** — unit & integration test runner (ESM/TS-native, fast, Jest-compatible API,
  first-class in a Turborepo/pnpm monorepo). The default for everything non-E2E.
- **React Testing Library** (+ `@testing-library/jest-dom`, `@testing-library/user-event`)
  on **jsdom** — component behaviour tests for `packages/ui` and client components.
- **vitest-axe** — automated accessibility assertions inside component tests (ties into the
  WCAG 2.2 AA requirement; see `accessibility.mdc`).
- **Playwright** (+ `@axe-core/playwright`) — end-to-end tests for the Next.js apps: real
  routing, RSC rendering, navigation, keyboard flows and page-level a11y scans.

Do not introduce Jest/Cypress/Enzyme — keep the stack consistent across the monorepo.

## What to test (by priority)

1. **Pure logic — always.** `packages/utils`, `packages/tradetracker` (feed parsing &
   normalization), `packages/cms` (query building, `market` filtering). Highest ROI; unit-test
   thoroughly including edge cases and malformed feed data.
2. **Shared UI components** in `packages/ui` — test **behaviour, not implementation**
   (what the user sees/does). Include a keyboard-interaction test and a `vitest-axe` check.
3. **Critical app flows** — a few Playwright smoke/E2E tests per app (page renders, primary
   navigation, key CTA, offer listing). Not every page.

## Conventions

- Co-locate unit/component tests as `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx` next to the source.
- Playwright E2E lives in `apps/<app>/e2e/` as `*.spec.ts`.
- Name tests by behaviour ("renders the CTA", "filters offers by market"), not by method name.
- Query by accessible role/label/text (RTL) — this doubles as an accessibility check. Avoid
  `data-testid` unless there is no accessible alternative.
- **Async Server Components:** don't over-mock them in unit tests. Extract logic into pure,
  testable functions (unit-tested) and cover the rendered result with Playwright.
- Every **bug fix ships with a regression test** that fails before the fix.
- Mock network/feeds at the boundary; never hit live TradeTracker/Sanity in unit tests. Use
  fixtures for feed XML and GROQ responses.

## Commands

```bash
pnpm test          # run unit/component tests (turbo → vitest) across the repo
pnpm test:e2e      # run Playwright E2E (per app)
```

Tests must pass before a change is considered done. Once the pre-commit hook (husky) lands,
the fast unit suite + lint run automatically on commit.
